name: 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate 5-dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
comment: The enzyme from Pseudomonas acts equally well on NAD+ or NADP+, while that from Erwinia chrysanthemi and Escherichia coli is more specific for NAD+.

references.title: An enzyme in the pectolytic pathway of Erwinia chrysanthemi: 3-keto-3-deoxygluconate oxidoreductase.
Polygalacturonic acid metabolism in bacteria. II. Formation and metabolism of 3-deoxy-D-glycero-2, 5-hexodiulosonic acid.
